ACT:
 Indian Income-tax Act, 1922, s. 10(2)(vii) and s. 34-Full disclosure of material facts to Income-tax Officer within meaning of s. 34(1)(a), what amounts to-Failure to show excess of price for which assets sold in return and further failure to show written down value amounts to failure to disclose facts-Tribunal must determine whether any profits are made under section 10(2) (vii)-Without this being first determined the High Court in reference under section 66(1) cannot decide whether there has been failure to disclose material facts.
 
